Subjects: Northampton, battle of; historical poems; allegories
_description: On the Battle of Northampton (1460) — twenty 8-line stanzas (ababbcbc, abababab)

TCD432.First Lines:
Of all mennys disposicion naturallPhilisophyrs wryten in euery
                    place…
TCD432.Last Lines:
…And illumyn hym with þe holy gosteHis reme to set in
                    perfyt charite
